type.name: type
type.description: Whether one or multiple items can be open

collapsible.description: Whether items are collapsible when type is single

components.description: A single item within an Accordion.

title.name: title
title.description: Header text displayed in the trigger

example:
<Accordion type="single" collapsible>
  <AccordionItem value="install" title="How do I install jc?">Run bun add jc.</AccordionItem>
</Accordion>

<Accordion type="multiple">
  <AccordionItem value="faq-1" title="Is jc free?">Yes, MIT licensed.</AccordionItem>
</Accordion>

title.name: title

headerAction.name: headerAction

components.description: A styled monospace code block with syntax highlighting.

inline.name: inline
inline.description: Whether to show a compact inline-style block

components.description: A minimal data table for displaying structured information.

rows.name: rows
rows.description: Row data (array of arrays matching column count)

monoFirstCol.name: monoFirstCol
monoFirstCol.description: Render first column in monospace font

example: <DataTable columns={["Command", "Description"]} rows={[["dev", "Start dev server"], ["build", "Production build"]]} monoFirstCol />

components.description: A rich profile card showcasing complex prop data structures.

online.name: online
online.description: Whether the user is currently online

contact.name: contact
contact.type: { email: string; phone?: string; address?: { street: string; city: string; zipCode: string; country: string } }

notifications.name: notifications
notifications.type: { email: boolean; push: boolean; sms: boolean; frequency: "instant" | "daily" | "weekly" }

metrics.name: metrics
metrics.type: { label: string; value: number; unit?: string; trend?: "up" | "down" | "flat" }[]
metrics.description: Key metrics displayed on the profile

onClick.name: onClick
onClick.description: Called when the profile card is clicked

onMessage.name: onMessage
onMessage.description: Called when the user clicks the message button

example: <ProfileCard name="Alice Johnson" role="admin" contact={{ email: "alice@example.com", phone: "+1 555-0123" }} online />
<ProfileCard name="Bob Smith" role="member" contact={{ email: "bob@example.com" }} metrics={[{ label: "Posts", value: 42 }, { label: "Followers", value: 1200, trend: "up" }]} />

<ProfileCard name="Charlie Dev" role="owner" contact={{ email: "charlie@acme.com", address: { street: "123 Main St", city: "Paris", zipCode: "75001", country: "France" } }} socialLinks={[{ platform: "github", url: "https://github.com/charlie" }, { platform: "twitter", url: "https://twitter.com/charlie" }]} verified />

propValues.name: Charlie Dev
propValues.contact: { email: "charlie@acme.com", address: { street: "123 Main St", city: "Paris", zipCode: "75001", country: "France" } }

components.description: A metric card displaying a key statistic with optional trend indicator.

example: <StatCard label="Bugs" value={3} change="-60%" trend="down" icon={Bug} tags={["critical", "ui"]} />

components.description: An informational callout banner with intent variants.

example: <Callout intent="info" title="Heads up">This feature is in beta.</Callout>
<Callout intent="success" title="Saved">Your changes have been applied.</Callout>
<Callout intent="error" icon={ShieldAlert}>Access denied. Contact your admin.</Callout>
